\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 In Unst?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Unst. Unst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Where in Unst was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The Westing. Westing. On the west side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Is it a village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Hamlet you call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You didn't move from there until 1909?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You are one of ten children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Are you in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I'm in the middle. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How do they go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I've had six sisters and four brothers. Oh - six - six sisters and three brothers. Four brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What's the gap between the oldest and the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Round about - twenty year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Do you know when your father was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, I - wait a minute. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 
If you wait a minute - he was sixty - about - sixty - 19 - 1955. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did he come from Unst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, he - I can tell you he came from the island of Yell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Fisherman. Yes, fisherman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did he have a croft then as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 We - we had a croft, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That would be when he was a bit older you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well, he - my mother - my mother's father owned-the croft you 
see and when he married he came to the - to my mother's house you see and - there's - you - really my mother's croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Then he would carry on fishing and crofting at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did he do any other sorts of jobs }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 besides}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  fishing and crofting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, fishing - fishing and crofting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Can you remember when your mother was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She lived 'til she was ninety-five. She was about - she would be about - born about the same time I think. 1855.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Unst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 From this particular - this was her father's croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She never went out to work I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh no. Oh no. No, no. She was always on the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Could you tell me how many rooms there were in the house on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Four. Four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How many of those were bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 There would be - one, two, three - actually the kitchen had to be used as a - a - as a bedroom. Two or three of the younger ones - boys.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So there was a kitchen and two bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 A kitchen - kitchen and three bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Besides your parents and brothers and sisters were there any other relatives living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 My - mother's - my aunt. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No. No room. There'd be no room with all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would she have sent the washing out or done that at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The washing? Oh - oh mother - oh - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She did all that at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did she make any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That would be knitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Knitting and - and making clothes you see for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Just knitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, and making clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She actually made suits and things as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your father do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, he had - made - made our shoes. The shoes or boots. No, no bootmakers then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 He made the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, he repaired shoes I should say. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house like cooking, cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No, he did all outside work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would he do decorating for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No. Not father. Mother and my aunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Nothing at all, not even lighting fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, oh
 yes. But the fire was never out you see. No, using peats you see - they covered - covered the - covered the coals with peat ash at night and then in the morning you stir it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Where did they get the peat from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 A way to - long way to go f
or peat, about - about two miles away to go for peat. Took the peats home during the summer. Enough to last you all winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was that a sort of common that the peat came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Peats were cut on the common. Each - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 each}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  crofter had a right to cut peat on the common.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Could you graze animals on the common as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. A certain number only. So many sheep and so many ponies - on the common.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your father help looking after the children, like helping them dress or looking after them if your mother had to go out to do something?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. Or sing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 He'd sing would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Old Shetland songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, generally sea - sea songs, yes sea songs. They were quite common in my youth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did they boys have to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You worked outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, the girls helped in the house but not the boys. They would do outside work. But not help in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You had to help on the croft - the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh absolutely. As soon as we were able. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How young would that be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Oh by the time was twelve, fetch water you see, we'd to - we used to go about - a hundred and fifty yards and fetch pails of water from the well. And fet
ch the - fetching peats. Peats were not inside, they were outside. That was the boys' work, fetching peats, fetching the water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 And the girls helped with the cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did - the girls helped their mother in the house. And learnt -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 And looking after the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, and learnt to spin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They had to spin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. Learn that at an early age you know. Yes. Oh - generally a Shetland girl can knit about eight or nine. Yes, she starts early.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would they spin from wool from their own sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How many sheep did you have on the croft?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 We generally had about forty I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's quite a lot isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, that's about average. Yes, about average.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How many people in your family could spin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Well - mother and aunt and then my sisters, they worked you see but they left when they were coming to nineteen or twenty. They'd go away you see. Because there was no room for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well there would sometimes be ten of you in the family but normally some had moved off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well, by the time the last one was born the oldest way away. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you expected to go to bed at a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, no fixed time, but generally about ten o'clock, ten to eleven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 And you'd put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was there a special washday every week when you'd all have fresh clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. Wash when you got a suitable day. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 
The weather, because all the drying had to be done outside. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 There was no room inside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So you had a plain breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Plain breakfast. Yes. Home baked scones and butter. And either tea or milk. Generally milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you not have porridge at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Very seldom. Porridge - porridge was - had porridge for supper. You know, about nine o'clock at night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What about the food for the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Well there'd always be potatoes and soup sometimes, potatoes and either fish - either fish or salt, or meat. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That - that'd be lamb or pork. Either fresh or salt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have another meal before supper?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 It was a tea. Tea. We called tea. It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 generally}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  about - five - five to six o'clock. And then it was - plain scones again. And oatcakes sometimes. And tea or milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So the main meal was the one at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Generally about one o'clock. But one - one to two o'clock, there was - a half an hour either way didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What time would breakfast be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Breakfast as generally about nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you all sit down together for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Oh yes. Then - as I say - it was rare when there was ten of our family there you see. Some would be gone by the time you - the younger ones were beginning to grow up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What did your mother cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 An open fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 A peat fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Peat fire, yes. Open peat fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How did she roast, did she have a hook or something hanging?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Well you get that, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Open fire. A hook - a hook hanging down which you could raise or lower you see. And - a griddle for - for - the flat pan you know, for - for scones and - a big iron pot for - potatoes and fish - and fish, so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 It must have been a lovely taste to the roasts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh well I suppose it did, had better appetite then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You never left anything uneaten then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Do you think your mother would have minded if you had?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No. Oh I don't know. We didn't seem - I didn't seem - I never was really hungry. We used to go through vast quantities of buttermilk. We never drank water. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 No, no for us buttermilk. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Yes. Sometimes whey, it was - that was the buttermilk when it was freshly - poured in boiling water you see and then - to curdle a bit on top and below was they whey. Sort of slightly sour a bit. But we never drank water. Buttermilk was different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Very seldom. Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What about rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, we occasionally had rabbits. Plenty of rabbits about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You used to catch them on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 We - we used to hunt them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No, well there was a dog sometimes did. I remember about - when I was probably about - eleven or twelve year old and brother of mine got a ferret. But they got a ferret. Nobody - all freedom there you see. Yes. Oh yes. You can have as many rabbi
ts as you like, as long as you could get them. Oh no, it was entire life of freedom. Wonderful freedom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you grow any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. We - we grew cabbage and turnips. But we always - occasionally we grew carrots but - cabbage and turnips you see we always grew that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You wouldn't have had any tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your mother bottle them or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 preserve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No. You see, we would have a yard of about - two - between two and three thousand cabbage,
 you see, which were - which we used partly and partly fed to the - to the cattle, during the winter. And turnips the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So you really had unlimited food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well - we did - we had unlimited food of a sort, you see, but very plain food. Yes. Very plain.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did she bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Yes, mother baked her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You had an oven as well then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Well she - she helped her own mother. The - there were - they probably had to change - she - help and bake you see and moth
er would do something else, or maybe the other way around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She didn't make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No, she didn't make jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did she make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 People in Shetland didn't make wine did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You had your own pigs and hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Pigs and hens and geese. We had some geese, we had about - I think about - three dozen at least. And we used to sell about - more than half of that. Each year at Christmas about. Used to get about two and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No. No goats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would it be the men or the women who looked after the animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
The men would look after the ponies or sheep. But the cattle - the cattle was purely - the ladies side of the question. They - they did all the milking. Oh yes. Yes. Oh a Shetland man in the covatry would never dream - milking a cow, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I don't know. I never learned milking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 When you were sitting down at meals did your parents mind if you talked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If we talked? No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Could you ask for some more food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Yes. Certainly, yes - oh yes. Yes. You - you were perfectly free, you could walk out and never say a thing. Yes, you could walk out and never say where you'd gone, never say when you'd come back. You wouldn't be asked. Oh no, complete freedom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you allowed to bring something to the table if you wanted to, like a book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh no. Oh no. Oh no. Well you - you never thought of bringing a book to table because - you were more engrossed in get
ting something in your stomach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were they strict about things like how you held your knife and fork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No, you pleased yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have set places or did you sit where you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Generally the children sat anywhere you see bu
t there were certain places which by custom was reserved for your parents. But - otherwise the children - children just sat anywhere that was nearest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 All the children came, you didn't make the youngest children eat separately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Not past a certai
n age. I don't think so. Of course I remember my father never give me a walloping in my life. No, but I remember my mother giving me a good hiding, for disobeying an order. Well she told me I was not to do something, and I did it and she'd warned me she'd
 give me a hiding, and I got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What sort of thing would they regard as really serious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's a very difficult question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Can you say what were the most important things they impressed on you about life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They never - they never impres
sed very - they never pressed anything special on us. We - as I say, we were free to feel our own way. And then, we all - we were always warned - if you did such and such a thing wrong - up to you. You got the worst of it, see that sort of thing, that sor
t of idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So you don't feel they had a very set idea of what they hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They had a - they hoped for the best. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If another child }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 hit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  you would they say you ought to hit back or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 They would allow you, you hit back. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
If one - one child - if one of my brothers hit me I could hit back you see, it'd be all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They didn't mind about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They let the brothers and sisters sort things out themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Sort things out themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you say that you got the ideas about how to behave from both your parents or one rather than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I should think - I should think equally from both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Do you think your mother was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, you could easy - easy person to talk to, but she could be very firm you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If you were worried about something you could go and talk to her about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No. It - each Shetlander is I think very much off - being on their own because I don't th
ink you'd go and talk to parents about anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The same with your father, you'd keep it to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Just the same. Yes, you wouldn't - you wouldn't ask them for their advice. Take their own advice and if you went wrong you just used to learn. Have to work - work it out for yourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would a birthday be any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No, only days which were different were - Christmas which was Yule of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yule is New Year is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, no, Christmas. Christmas. 
We - we - the New Year was separate but - Christmas day or Yule was the most important day in the year you see. It was not the Christian festival by any means. Church wasn't open, no. Nothing at all. You were - you were out playing football or kicking a b
all about. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Firing off}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
 - shooting off shotguns you know. General jollifications and a dance at night. As you grew older. But - New Year much the same but on a lesser scale. The fishermen used to have their Johnsmas which is about the beginning of July. I thi
nk. They used to have a feast among the fishermen at that time. But a lot of it's dying out now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You said your father sang, did anyone in the family play an instrument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you all have a sort of family sing-song together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 It was a solo?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, no. My - my father would - oh I don't know - sing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 ing with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
the kishies, straw baskets. Well he'd make them during the winter night sometimes you see, as he made them he would sing a sea shanty sometimes. Picked - picked up from the boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 This was in the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, in the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I've heard that sometimes a lot of people would gather in one croft and sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Ah - that's a - that's a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 ceildh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 , that's a - that's south but not - not our way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They don't do it here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, no. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would your parents play any games like dominoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. They were spinning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Always working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The womenfolk were always spinning or knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would they read at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, they would read - read on - on a Sunday. They wouldn't spin on a Sunday, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you have newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 We got - we got the Shetland newspaper every week. That was all. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 On Sundays would you read aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. Never read aloud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Can your remember when you were a boy there being a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Can you tell me at all what happened, were there a great many people came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well all the male population of - the surrounding district would arrive there. And -
 arrive at the house. The minister would be there and he'd give a short service and then - generally there was no road from the house to the cemetery, the cemetery might be - two miles away and - these men would carry the coffin, you see, in relays. Walk 
so far and then change over. And at the graveside there was a few words said but - they always stood until the turfs been put on the grave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Whatever the weather was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. Had to be there for the - whatever like the weather was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you visit relations, did you go out to visit relatives or neighbours very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Not so much - we visited - neighbours. For instance there was good friend about half a mile away, with an old man and a son, they used - very good players of the f
iddle. And - we used to go there pretty often, about once a fortnight you know, and spend an evening there or something. Between six and seven until eleven o'clock. And he'd play the fiddle to us you see, that's a very common thing for to for to go to nei
ghbour's house and sit there. You see, you - you didn't go and knock at the door, you just simply opened the door and walked in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So you'd just go and have a chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. And - the young women of the place, they would go to the house you see and sit and knit. And gossip I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That would be in the winter evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 In the winter evenings, oh yes, not in summer evenings 'cos everybody was so busy on summer evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Working on the crofts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Oh you had too much to do about the farm, you couldn't get away on the summer evenings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you say people helped each other a lot at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well - they would go and help each other with croft work if - some - some old body were
 left by herself or - or a pair of old people left by themselves, some of the young ones of the district they would go there and - and - work the croft for them to a great extent, the hard work you know. And they would gather together half a dozen young f
ellows and go and cut their peats for them. Yes, oh yes. That used to be common. Yes, I've worked many a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946  long}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
 day just for nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would they give you some food if you were working for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They - yes, they generally give you - your lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 It must be nice in some ways working in groups like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes. That - that still happens. Yes, that still happens. I was up in Unst this year and - a fellow I was very well acquainted with, he's almost as old as I am, he wasn't able to 
cut his peats this year. And he came down to Lerwick to see the doctor. And when he came back his two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 neighbour men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
 had cut his peats for him. For nothing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were there any shops near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 There's a shop - a general merchant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 s shop about - about half a mile away, and another one about - three miles away. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 Pnacial}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
 one was about three miles away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you sometimes come into Lerwick to shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh no, no, no. That's - that's out of the question. Forty miles from here. Oh yes, forty mile by sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was Baltasound the main shopping centre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No, Uyeasound was nearer, Baltasound was six mile away. Uyeasound was nearer, only three mile away. And they kept - anything we would probably need. Even kept - whisky and beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's just a village is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
It's not too much a village, it's a scattered place. Like if you look across there you see the crofts scattered around the shore there. Generally - anything from a quarter to a half a mile between each house. But hamlet is - is hardly
 the correct word, you know, it's a district you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You never left the island as a boy, you didn't go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You say you didn't work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you put on different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Generally put on our
 best suits. But - if we weren't at church we might have a walk around, but you didn't - you didn't do anything like shooting or fishing or - any work at all. And the womenfolk -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well, only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 quietly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 , we weren't supposed to do. We'd play games - games - some outdoor games. Generally went for a walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your parents often go to church or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 My father used to go regularly to church. But my mother - I don't remember her ever going to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She'd be cooking possibly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She - yes, be home. Father used to go regularly to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was that the parish church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, parish church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did they send you to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, I think I was - I was - a year or two at Sunday school. But it was three miles away, we had to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have any annual outings from your Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were there any sort of clubs attached to the church that you joined?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 When you had meals did your parents say grace at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would they teach you to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your father take any special interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You don't know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 His views - well - mostly Shetland }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  all Liberal you see, I suppose he voted Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Why do you think he supported the Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The Liberals were responsible for passing the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 rofters }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 ct you see, which give the crofters security of tenure. Alth
ough actually - actually it was a Conservative measure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your mother take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She followed your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh she - she - she never vote. Oh that time when the women didn't have the vote. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I suppose they didn't really have any time to go out to enjoy themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. My mother never - never went any - any visits from - my mother especially never went out, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were there any local clubs to join or anything like that if you wanted to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Well sometimes about - sometime about 1910 - or thereabout we had a - institute built, where we could ago and have a dance occasionally. Christmas night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were there any pubs on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Licensed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  grocer's shop, you'd
 one pub - one pub at Baltasound, the grocer's. - licensed grocer's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 But they're not the centres that they are in English villages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh no. No, no, no, no. No, they're - a crowd didn't gather there at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If people did gather together it would be more in a croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 In - in a croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was there any sort of organised sports, like hunting together, there's nothing much to hunt I suppose except rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, the only organised sport was a regatta. Which was held each summer. Sailing races and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 rowing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  races and races there were. That was only organised sport there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were your parents interested in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 As a child you say you were very free to do what you wanted, were you mainly playing around with your brot
hers and sisters or were there neighbours that you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
There was a house close to us where here was a young family and - my brother and I had - the two brothers from there, we were generally together. Playing games. We lived - about half a m
ile from beautiful sand you know. We'd play among the rocks and along the sand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were there any special games you played as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 We practiced long jumping, high jumping and we - we had a children games there I quoits. Set up a pin then throw - 
throwing stones at it you see. Three stones each. Called it quoits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Any toys you had to make yourself.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh absolutely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What sort of things would you make?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Catapult was the about the first. And a bow and arrow. Yes. Yes, I think that was the first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 With a rod in the sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Well I by the time - by the time I left Unst there was fly fishing for sea trout. We fished for sea trout in the sea here you know, with flies. Yes. I've fished all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have any hobbies as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No. I don't think I had. Nothing special. There's so much to do you see, if you let a boy loose in the country he can enjoy himself even if he's walking about kicking an old can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You were interested in the wild life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The surroundings, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I suppose you knew all the names of the birds and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. The only thing I didn't know, about me, I didn't know the name of the flowers. I knew the Shetland name of them b
ut not the English name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Are they all different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, they're all different. Even the names of our birds are different you know. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Do you think that you were unusual in appreciating the wild life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh I think so. I think I - I like it for the bird - wildlife you see. I'm very keen and interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Most people just take it for granted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You'll find about - you'll find two people in every five - very keen on ornithology up here. They know all the birds know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you say that your parents had any special friends, neighbouring crofters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No, they were - the crofters were usually very good friends. Oh yes, helped each other you see, if you wanted a loan of anything you went to the croft as they had it, you - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 you\rquote d}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  get a loan of it, you see, son on - so on they went like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would they have anybody in for a meal or offer them something to drink, a neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh - oh yes, if you went along to a house and they were sitting down to - to lunch 
or anything like that you'd be asked go partake. And - at - at Christmas - Christmas morning we generally went around all the houses with a bottle of whisky. To - yes, to wish them a happy Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 And you didn't have to be invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh no. No, no, you never did - never were invited. You just simply walked in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Some of those friends of your parents, they would play the fiddle and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. I - I used to play the fiddle and my brother, just died this past year, he - he was a better player than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You played the fiddle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 When did you learn then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
You just - started from nothing and you just tried - you'd no teacher you see. I packed it up in 1914. Well I - I went away - I - I had to leave Shetland see in 
the Army. And - I was in the Territorials before the war you see. We were called up in the service you see, 'Cos I went out for three years so - notice served when I came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You said before that nobody in the family could play an instrument, only you in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The - oh - well - my brother and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You both played the fiddle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. We both played. Oh you got - you got somebody to play the fiddle in house - in almost any house in Shetland at that time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you just sit listening to the fiddle or did people dance when they played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No. You - you'd listen - listen to them playing you see and take a turn with playing. You know this past - this past winter there was a competition down in Perth. Scotch fiddlers for - for the bes
t fiddlers among the - the Scotch players. One of the judges was Yehudi Menhuin. Great }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 violinist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
. A Shetlander won it. A real - a real good player.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You were talking to me about the lairds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was there a laird on Unst?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. But - h
e was a Shetlander. I don't - if there were one - one, two, three lairds or Unst. And probably of our. But the one that dealt with the fishing was actually Shetlander. And - he owned the boats you see and - the fisherman got half share of the catch. And o
f course he fixed the price.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 But he did very well did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. His - his grandsons are still up there yet on Unst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did the lairds keep themselves to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Yes, even he was a Shetlander and come up by - he - no use for you. No. He was a step up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was there anyone else on the Island who felt themselves superior in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Well the minister always did. The minister always did. And the - the schoolmasters, when I was a boy, the schoolmasters generally came from the mainland school and - they were simply looked up to. Or looked down on us, I don't know which.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you taught to raise your cap to people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes - we did as boys, but - I remember meeting one of the lairds and his wife when I was a young 
man. I raised my cap to them both and said good morning. He said, good morning but he didnot raise his cap. So next time I met him I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 did not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  raise it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 It was really an equal society, do you think everybody thought of themselves as equals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, they - unequal at that time but now they're very much equal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They were unequal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were these people superior, were there any very poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Oh you occasionally - you occasionally got an old maid here or there or some old woman or some old man or maybe - that }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 did not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  have much and left alone you see. And neighbours tried to help her sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They didn't look down on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 There were cotters as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Some of them were cotters, som
e of them - but - some of them were cotters and some of them had a croft you see and the men - they maybe had no family and - the man had died and left -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 In England there's a strong }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 distinction}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  between craftsmen and other workers, would you say that applied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. It }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 doesn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
 apply here. Every Shetlander is more or less a craftsman. Because - a crofter had to - he'd to mend his own boots, the boots of the family or his family, make his own clothes and do repair work, joiner work and even brickwork a
bout his house. So he had to be bit of a craftsman. But of course there was some good craftsmen and some poor ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were there some families who were called rough and some who were respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, some - there were some families which - were - quite more - refined more reasonable. Other ones were - were rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What sort of things would you think would make the difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well their attitude to other people, you see, their attitude to live would be different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Can you give me an example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, I'd have to think sometime before I could give you an example.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So really it's a question of character?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 It's a question of character. Not so much your environment as character.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Some were quarrelsome?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Some were quarrelsome and some were not. I - I think - I think that - yes, I think that you'll find that in any community. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you brought up with an idea of what a real gentleman was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. You were - you were brought up to make your own way in life.
 Just - if you failed by the way it was your own fault. If you - improved and got on - so much the better. You were out on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have any policemen on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 We'd one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 policeman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  for the three north isles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What did the people think about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They just paid no heed to him. He - he was - he was quite a friendly chap. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 He hadn't much to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 He - no, he had nothing to do, or practically nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Your parents obviously had to work very hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you feel at all resentful about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No. My mother lived until she was ninety-four. Yes. My aunt lived 'til she was eighty-three. And my - my father died when he was about sixty. Or sixty-five, I'm not quite sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If ther
e was a family in the district, or a person, who behaved in a way that everybody disapproved of very much, did you - was there any special way of dealing with that, like sort of putting them to Coventry or rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well - we generally just ignore
d them - avoided them you see. But - generally speaking there were not too - they liked to live in peace you see. You didn't want anybody interfering with you and you didn't want to - you didn't ; interfere with any other person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I suppose you had to try and get on with everybody because it was a smallish community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
It was smallish community, you tried to do your best. But - if - if one proved impossible - some person proved impossible - well you just ignored them. Yes. That's was all. That's all they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How old would you be when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 We didn't go to school \lquote til we were seven. Yes. And I left when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 This was on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 On the island, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was it boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Boys and girls. There was about forty when I went to school. The school has been closed now - for lack of pupils for about fifteen year.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have to walk a long way to get to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I had to walk about - nearly three quarters of a mile. Which was - which was spl
endid. Because it'd give you some - fresh air in the mornings. Yes, oh I enjoyed my school. I really did, I must say it was about the happiest time of my life. When I went to school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You liked the teachers, was there one teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, there 
was - the first teacher, I didn't like him at all. But - I like it - I liked the school, I liked the company of all the children and I like it - learn different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Why didn't you like the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well he was one these impossible people. Yes. He got into trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You say you left when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you have liked to have gone on at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh teaching was finished, I - the last year I was at school I was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Euclid
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  and algebra - the country school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You were saying you were a pupil teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, the last year I was. Last year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you enjoy doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, I enjoyed it. Teacher told me he couldn't teach me - teach me much more. I'm not boasting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you go on and do any night school at a later stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, later on I went to night school, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 forget}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  what I took there, bookkeeping or something. Yes. Oh something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have any regrets really about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. I regret that I couldn't know more about ornithology and botany at school, things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So you really had to teach yourself at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well - it was generally just the three R's you know, reading, writing and arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If you were interested in something special, like you were, could you get books and read it for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. You couldn't - no, no books available. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Terrible isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. There's a change now. Books are simply flung at you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You left school and was that when you went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Edinburgh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No, I was at home for a few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Helping on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well, helping on the croft, in summertime I would get a job - a job of some - odd jobs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What sort of odd jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Let me see, I was - we started being - telegraph messenger first of all, and then - couple of years I was in a grocer's shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That was on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 On the island, yes. I think two years I was in the - in a butcher's shop. Selling butcher's meat. And the last - yes. On the island.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you enjoy work, when you first started as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, I - I enjoyed it all right. I - I didn't - I have since. I had the big town you know. I've always liked a big town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That's when you went to Edinburgh, you preferred that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Yes, oh - I went to Edinburgh and went up to a small place called - Broxburn, and then I went to - company, dairy company, and then went across to Ayrshire and Glasgow. And from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 there}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  to Tranent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What were you doing there with this dairy company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I - the - a shop like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Lipton's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 A big sort of chain store?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. And then they opened a branch up in Lerwick and I come up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So that's how you came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I come back up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 And they were kind of grocers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Oh yes, sort of grocers. Milk - sugar, condensed milk, tea, coffee - margarine and butter, all that, just that sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What sort of hours did you have to work at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Eight o'clock in the morning \lquote til eight at night. And - ten o'clock on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you have to live in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Oh no. No. You - you had your breakfast before you arrived there you see. And you got an hour at lunchtime but you had half an hour at tea time, in the shop, made the tea in the shop. But - oh I don't know, it's - I enjoyed it quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 How many other shop assistants would there be in these shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Generally two or three. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That was nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Aye, it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was there this sort of thing that you speak a kind of secret language that the customers can't understand, did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If you switch that off I'll tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Have you ever read H.G. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Well\rquote s History of Mr Polly?}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, I've read -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Do you think that's a fair picture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. It all depends on how you look at these - pictures. You know, one of the most remarkable stories ever I read }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  - Eskimo by Peter Corcoran, I think he made it into a - into a picture - a film. It was a most remarkable story you know. I enjoyed that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What was that about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 It's all about Eskimos. Eskimo - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So until 1914 you worked in this shop here in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Can you tell me something about the town at that time, there were a lot of tenements, were there a lot of poorish people in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Not many, not many, not much more than there is today but - the - the houses were not so good you see, a lot of new houses have been built at the back in there. The population probably was about four thousand or four and a half thousand which was i
ncreased during the summer to about six thousand. How the town is about six thousand residents. But we had quite a lot of fun in the shop because - the - about the beginning of June and there used to be a huge number of Dutch boats come in here. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Well at that time the price of sugar was tuppence and in Holland it was fivepence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
So they used to come along and buy sugar you know, wanted about ten pound and it\rquote d all be in a box. And we used to learn all about Dutch money. And like by the Dutchman. And occasiona
lly smuggle - smuggle some tobacco off them. Got an old chap to bring me some gin one day and he come in quite coolly and he said, look what I - he slipped it on the counter. Oh hold about a bottle, two bob for a bottle of gin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was there much going on in the way of entertainment in the town at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
At - I don't know what - good number of dances going, during the wintertime. In the summer we didn't have much time. Finished at eight o'clock. In the evening, and Saturday night well as - after ten before we finished. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 But then after five o'clock, you have your - especially on the Saturday - if you wanted to move along the street you had to walk very, very slowly, the main street here was jammed full of people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 The shops were all - all open }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  eight. And now you go, after teatime the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  - it is dead. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was there a theatre or music hall or cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh a picture house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Cinema.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you have gone to that quite frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I went about once a week. Take a girl and go to the pictures once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 That was about the one sort of entertainment you could go to really was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Or go dancing. Oh maybe dance a fortnight or something like that. But - when we had a half day you see - an hour or 
two we had spare after the shop closed - we really enjoyed it. But nowadays they get so much spare time. I - they don't know what to do with themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was it easy to make friends or did you know people before you came to the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, I didn't know anybody before I came to town. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 
You make friends very, very easily here. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 People are very friendly. I must say that for us, we're very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You said you lived in lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes. Yes. The landlady came from a country district, here in Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did she have several lodgers or were you by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No, I think she'd another fellow besides me. Yes, she - the first - there was two of us but then I went to a larger house afterwards. After I came back from Army I went to a larger house. And there was generally four of us. Four lodgers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You came back here and in 1919 you started this work as a car hirer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. I was discharged out of the Army 1917. And I went back to shop again. I didn't - I don't know - I didn't like it, I
 wanted my freedom so I - I started this car hiring business. 'Cos you know a company fund couldn't pay. Oh so I became agent for grocery firm first and then for a brewery firm, an agent for that. Which paid very well. And - then for a whisky firm in - in
 1939. As a matter of fact I'm still agent for them. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So you didn't do the car hiring for a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I did for a long time. For about - forty - about forty-five year I did that. Agent as well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 People here seem to have so many different jobs at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Well, yes, well you sunk a few hundred pounds in a car, well you had to try and get it back keep it so it wasn't paying you very well. But - if you got a job besides kept me going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 And then you stayed in lodgings until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Oh yes. Married in 1922. I've three in the family. Yes. The oldest is - he's county surveyor. He's civil - he's a civil engineer and his brother is an architect. And my daughter, as I told you before, she was a schoolteacher. A B.Sc. She's married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What does her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Her husband - is - well he's quite well-to-do. He's got a draper's shop there at the Grand Hotel. D.G. Tay. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 So they've all done terrible well haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, they've done 
all right. I've a - I - my wife was an Aberdeen - fortnight ago. She - seeing off my grandson, he's twenty-five, he's married. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 He's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  - he's a graduate teacher in English and he's off to Turkey. Teach English in Turkey. Yes. We'd a - we had a grandson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your wife work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 My wife went away to see him before he went you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your wife work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She used to be in a shop. Confectionary shop. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Could you tell me about the jobs that your brothers and sisters had, did some of them stay on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
Oh no. One of my sisters stayed on the croft some time. No, two sisters stayed on the croft for some time and then they packed up. The croft is empty now. Oh yes. For about sixteen, seventeen year. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Could you tell me what your brothers did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Well my two brothers went to Canada, you see, they - they are farming. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 
And they did very, very well. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 One of them is married, and the other one never married. But - he was older than me. They both died this last winter. Died wit
hin six months of each other. But they did very well. And - my other - my oldest brother he was - he was on the ship which sunk the U - '59, the U-boat - that's in the first world war, the U-boat that sunk the - the Hampshire, the - the boat that Lord }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Kitchener}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
 was on. Well they - they sunk that boat and then he went on another boat and he was torpedoed and lost in the English Channel. And my wife had a brother killed in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Gallipoli}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 . He used - he came - he was with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 Australians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 , he'd gone to Australia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What was that brother before he went to the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 He was a shopkeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did any of the sisters work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Let me see, I'll have to think hard about - about this. My oldest sister married, she's long dead. She married policeman. Now my other si
ster died young - two - the other - next two died. Yes. And - my other sister was married here in the town and she died about two years ago. She's a daughter - she was a schoolteacher but she - she's married to a banker and lives in Grantham on Spey near 
Lincoln.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Amazingly scattered isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh - it's always the same, the Shetland families scattered all over the place. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 They have always been very good at that for a long time ago, do you feel that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You mean I - when you were a you
ng man here you were at odds to move out, I - don't know why. I was within an ace of going to British Columbia in 1913. Yes, I thought seriously about it. Another chap and me were going away. Some bother, it fell through. No we had an urge to move you kno
w. I don't know - why but after a bit we settled down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Is it partly because it's a hard life do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No, it's an urge to move, it's an urge to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  the world. You see, I I've been fortunate in keeping my family in the - they all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 live}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  here in
 the town. Yes. That's why - up for a boy of fourteen you see. The hard work would commence in March on a fine day we were getting out the manure from the byre and put onto the fields. And then it was all turning of the - we'd no ploughs, used to turn it 
a
ll by hand. And it would take about five weeks altogether. And then you - you were free again until August when you're cutting the hay. And by the time that - by the middle of October you'd be cutting the hay, cutting the corn, gathered it all into the cr
oft, gathered the potatoes, which had to be - done by hand of course. And take up the turnips. Then you're free - free to take your holiday in winter. That's about the time you did your shooting in the - winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You had far more freedom than later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
You had absolute freedom. Ass I say, you - you go out leave the house and - you wouldn't say when you'd be back and they wouldn't worry. You wouldn't say when you were coming back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you take part in any social activities connected with the church when you were in Lerwick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you connected with the church at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 What about politics, did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 At that time, before 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, I thought of - well of course I couldn't vote at that time. But - I thought -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 As}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  a lodger you had to specially request a vote}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14829982\charrsid1456946 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946  didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, request a vote, yes. I've always - I've always voted Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Why do you think you differed from your father in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14425954\charrsid1456946 
Why do ; well I've explained why he - the Liberals pass a - a crofter's act therefore all Shetland and Orkney - were Liberal and they still vote, together - still for the Liberal. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
That is the sole reason. Yes. But they're giving the union too much po
wer now. And until they curtail the power of the union we're up against it. You know. The master - the - the servant can't rule the master. If you employ somebody you must tell them what to do and if he doesn't do that he - you'd be in a position to - to 
push him off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Are there any trade unions that have any strength up here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Oh yes, there's - there's the - General Transport and Workers Union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 In the harbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. Over there, they sometimes go on strike for some nonsense or other. Stevedores.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did you ever come across the shop assistants union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 
No. No. We haven't got any shop assistants up here. No. You see, if you start at the top you've the T.U.C. Then you have - unions. And then you've the shop stewards. And below them you
've the unofficial strikers. They're all a law unto themselves. That's it, yes. And the poor old boss looking at it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Before you went to school, were you given lessons by your parents, for example in the alphabet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes. School age then 7.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Was your school a public or a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Public.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would the teachers punish girls with the strap like the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. Seldom girls were strapped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did they single out any children for different treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes, at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did they visit the school or talk to the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did the children at the school split up into different gangs (e.g. based on different villages)?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 While you were at school, did you have a part time job or any means of earning money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 When you were working as a shop assistant from 1909-14, can you remember what you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 20/- a week. Digs. were 14/-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you send some of this to your parents.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you given any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No. One week per year, no pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you apprenticed as a shop assistant at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If you had been asked before 1918 to divide society into different social classes, which would you have said the main classes were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Would you have thought it possible for a person to move from one of these classes to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 If your mother was unwell, did a neighbour or relative ever come in to help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 She was never unwell, lived to 95!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 A part from your parents and your aunt, did you have other relatives living nearby and did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Only cousins, very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 I don't think your parents were ever helped by the parish - am I right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 You are right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Do you remember any times when your mother would eat less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your parents give you any pocket money as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did they discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6959797 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6053371 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7107485\charrsid1456946 Did your parents belong to any savings clubs, such as a sick club or funeral club?
